<div id="peerReviewProcess">
<h3>Peer Review Process</h3>
<p><strong>Editorial process</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Reception</strong></p>
<p><em>Praxis Filosófica</em> journal will attend the sending of documents according to the order of arrival. After acknowledging receipt, the document will begin the editorial process with the editor\'s review. This review has a maximum time of 1 month.</p>
<p><em><strong>Are excluding criteria for the acceptance of documents: </strong></em></p>
<ul>
<li class="show">The issue does not correspond to the scientific field of journal editing.</li>
<li class="show">The writing exceeds the established extension.</li>
<li class="show">It does not use the reference type and APA citation sixth edition.</li>
<li class="show">It does not send the complete documentation.</li>
<li class="show">Do not send the writing in the required support (word format).</li>
<li class="show">There are problems of plagiarism or auto-plagiarism, identified by softwar turnitin.</li>
<li class="show">Peer evaluators conceptually reject the document.</li>
<li class="show">The document has been published in advance, partially or totally.</li>
<li class="show">The articles do not contain research or philosophical reflection.</li>
<li class="show">Do not comply with the intellectual property clause.</li>
<li class="show">Articles that, after having made the respective corrections, continue to present problems in their content (errors in the argumentative structure and syntax errors) may be rejected.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. Arbitration</strong></p>
<p>If the article meets the minimum reception requirements and is consistent with the subject of the journal, the document will be sent for evaluation; The time used for the evaluation can take from 1 to 2-3 months.</p>
<p>The <em>Praxis Filosófica</em> journal performs the review of documents through a "double blind" arbitration process. The articles will be evaluated by one or two anonymous academic pairs who will not know the identity of the author and, upon receiving the results of the evaluation, the author will not know the identity of the evaluator (s).</p>
<p>The evaluating pair has an evaluation format designed by the editorial team of the journal, which is sent together with the arbitration request letter and a pdf copy of the anonymous author\'s article.</p>
<p><strong>3. Opinion</strong></p>
<p>After receiving the evaluation, the editor will review the evaluation with the objective of informing the author if the article was approved, rejected or approved with corrections that will be indicated in the evaluation letter. The evaluations are designed with the aim of analyzing the argumentative and stylistic structure of the writing; In addition, it allows the author tools to improve their research work and throw new perspectives.</p>
<p>Authors should bear in mind that once the publication of the article is approved, the editor may include said article in the edition (number) that he considers pertinent according to editorial criteria of the content of the Journal. Therefore, it will not necessarily be published in the immediately following edition.</p>
<p>The Editorial Committee will decide, based on the respective reports, the convenience of publishing the received documents. In no more than six months after receipt of the original, the director will inform the author of the final decision and, in case this is favorable, the foreseeable information of the number in which it will be published. If necessary, the author may request a definitive version of the writing based on the considerations of the observations of the evaluating pair; the delivery of this new revised version does not necessarily imply its publication, since it must be revised again to verify that the comments of the peer reviewers were taken into account.</p>
</div>
